category: FUN WITH THE PERIODIC TABLE
category comment: 

clue: It's the only element on the chart with exactly the same name as a planet in our solar system

response: mercury

clue: Cs is listed as an alkali one, Co, as a transition one

response: a metal

clue: 1 of the only 2 letters not found in the abbreviations of elements with atomic numbers up to 100

response: J (or Q)

clue: After helium, it's the Next noble gas on the table

response: neon

clue: The seventh period begins with francium, followed by this element discovered in France in 1898

response: radium

